# 8bitcomputer-DLS
This project is made in Digital Logic Sim (DLS)

This repository documents my journey building a simple **8-bit computer** using only NAND gates in **Digital Logic Sim**.

## About
The project is a step-by-step exploration of digital logic, CPU design, and 8-bit computing, built entirely from scratch.  

## Status
Work in progress. Stay tuned for updates! ðŸ˜Š
## Architecture & Features
This project uses a **Minimal Instruction Set Computing (MISC)** architecture, currently supporting **22 instructions**.
Program memory is implemented as a **256x16 ROM**, allowing storage of up to 256 instructions, each 16 bits wide.
